description:
Skittles Cookies. Caramel Apple Oreos. White Chocolate M&M's. Potato chips that make your mouth cold with the same sensation you get from ice cube gum. I spent months searching the globe for the rarest snacks, candies, chocolates, and drinks I could find. These came from all different countries, and not surprisingly, when some arrived, they'd been quite shaken up. Some of the drink cans were clearly beaten and weathered. A few of the chip bags had expanded and then been crushed, likely from altitude changes from flights. But, ultimately, they all landed safely in my kitchen. Watch me taste and break down all of them!

On a separate note, I want to offer a MASSIVE congratulations to our two winners, both of whom I will be sending (with their +1) to a three Michelin starred meal. If you missed it, I gave away a three Michelin starred meal in one of our recent videos (but I ended up giving it to two people cause I love you all and couldn't help myself): 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o0CpeM4Wq0c&t 

Nathan will be going to the Netherlands with his father to a restaurant called The Liberije (which serves food out of a former prison). It looks mind-blowing. Madison, on the other hand, will be bringing her mother to Eleven Madison Park in New York City. I am hopeful they'll both take a short clip to share with us all once they experience these dinners, but I have reached out to them both separately already to set these dinners up. Both of you, please comment below so people can congratulate you! Also, I want to give a final thanks to my friend at Raremunchiez who helped me to secure some of these snacks. https://raremunchiez.com

SUBSCRIBE TO CATCH GORDON RAMSAY
